    <h2>History</h2>

    <p>Every SRFI is hosted on Github, but if you'd like a complete
      archive of all SRFI documents and code, please download <a
href="srfi.tgz">srfi.tgz</a>.</p>

    <p>
      The SRFI process  has been important to the development of
      some of the official Scheme standards, including <a
      href="http://www.r6rs.org/">R<sup>6</sup>RS</a> and <a
      href="http://r7rs.org">R<sup>7</sup>RS</a>.  It has been
      running <a href="srfi-history.html">since 1998</a>, and there
      have been many <a href="srfi-editors.html">different editors</a>.</p>

